OL,3,CRoyal Welsh Show could lose over #1m
OL,4,Cahead of school term changes
OL,6,FThe society is supported by the
OL,7,Fteaching unions, who say that there is
OL,8,Fno evidence to show that having a
OL,9,Fshorter summer holiday improves the
OL,10,Fperformances of pupils.
OL,12,FLaura Doel, director of the National
OL,13,FAssociation of Headteachers in Wales
OL,14,Fsaid: "As a union, we believe that any
OL,15,Fchanges in education must have the
OL,16,Fbest interests of learners at heart.
OL,17,FAnd there's been no evidence to
OL,18,Fsuggest that changing the school year
OL,19,Fwould have any academic benefit.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/10
